The family of a baby and toddler discovered alone on the streets of Suffolk has been located. The little girls were found with no guardians in sight around 9.30am in Crown St West, Lowestoft. One was thought to be around three years old and the other less than a year old. Both were unharmed and were looked after at a police station until they were reunited with their family before midday. Suffolk Police has thanked the public for their help. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.